With Perl!

Make some datasets:
mkdit data
perl -le'my $sz=512; for my $i (1..100) { my $s = $i*$sz; system("./gen_random_ints", $s, "data/dataset_$s.dat") or printf $!;  }'


run tests: (results helpfully printed as count,nanos.micros,millis.seconds to stderr)
perl -le'my $sz=512; for my $i (1..100) { my $s = $i*$sz; system("./mergesort", "data/dataset_$s.dat", "data/dataset_$s_sorted.dat") or printf $!;  }' > /dev/null
